	lect:lecture_id"14_X1031";
	sylb:summary "This course is open not only for international students who are coming to Japan to join EBA(University Consortium for Evidence Based Approach to the emergent issues in Asia) fieldwork activities but also for students who plan to come to Japan for doing an internship or for working in the company in the near future. The purpose of this course is to provide students with Japanese preliminary level including useful expressions for daily activities (e.g. eating out, shopping, asking for directions among others). Students are expected to be able to communicate comfortably with local Japanese by using these expressions towards the end of the course.

Notice Students who belong to EBA partner universities in ASEAN countries have priority over Keio Students. Keio Students can join this course only if there are seats available.

";
